parameters: "Kouzou-san, thank you for your hard work today as well."\n<Yukine>\F[3]
"Hmm, I guess you still can't see me, huh?"\n<Yukine>\F[8]

"Sigh, you really can't hear me, huh? I wish we could have a
chat once in a while."\n<Yukine>\F[10]

"Today we had another family come to give thanks. It's true,
the deity of this place really does bless us. Maybe when I
have a child, I should ask Yukine-sama for a blessing?"\n<Shrine Maiden>

"You'll be most welcome when that time comes. But it'll be a
little lonely if you quit being a miko... not that you can
hear my voice, though."\n<Yukine>\F[3]

"Yukine-sama. Please grant me a good match. If possible, I'd
like someone with a high income, tall, and handsome."\n<Shrine Maiden>

"Hmm... that might be difficult with the blessings I can
bestow. I can protect children, though."\n<Yukine>\F[7]

"Even though it's a small shrine, there are so many
visitors. My grandmother said she did her Shichi-Go-San here
too..."\n<Shrine Maiden>
"I remember that time. It feels somewhat nostalgic."\n<Yukine>\F[3]

"I wonder if my child will also celebrate Shichi-Go-San
here? Just kidding..."\n<Shrine Maiden>

"Ehehe, when that time comes, I'll do my best to make sure
they grow up healthy."\n<Yukine>\F[2]

"It's peaceful today as well. The breeze feels nice, I wish
days like this would continue."\n<Yukine>\F[1]

"Yukine-sama, Yukine-sama, thank you for curing my child's
illness. I will never forget this kindness for as long as I
live."\n<The girl's mother>

"Thank you, God... Hey, Mom. Did God really cure my
illness?"\n<Girl>

"Yes, the god of this place. Yukine-sama cured you. This god
is famous for being kind and helping children. Many other
children have prayed here and been cured just like you."\n<The girl's mother>
"Wow, that's amazing. So that Onee-san cured me."\n<Girl>

"Onee-san...? The priest over there looks like an old man to
me. Maybe you mean that shrine maiden? She doesn't quite
look like an Onee-san though."\n<The girl's mother>

"No, not them. I'm talking about the Onee-san sitting over
there in white. Look, you can see her, right?"\n<Girl>

"Sorry dear, it seems Mommy can't see her. Ah... that's
right, now that you're cured, shall we have stew today?"\n<Girl's Mother>
"Yay, stew! I love Mommy's stew♥"\n<The girl's mother>

(Her illness was properly cured. She seems to have fully
recovered, and it looks like my efforts were worth it.)\F[2]

"...But it's been a while since I met a 'child who can see'.
Onee-san, huh? It makes me happy. Maybe I'll take a little
walk around the shrine."\n<Yukine>\F[1]
